<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-18597] max-buffer-utilization-percent is always 0</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-18597</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;see &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/516d5240b98916feb3e51c8a143dede05a4edad1/core/src/main/scala/kafka/log/LogCleaner.scala#L127&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/516d5240b98916feb3e51c8a143dede05a4edad1/core/src/main/scala/kafka/log/LogCleaner.scala#L127&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; private def maxOverCleanerThreads(f: CleanerThread =&amp;gt; Double): Int =&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; &#160; cleaners.foldLeft(0.0d)((max: Double, thread: CleanerThread) =&amp;gt; math.max(max, f(thread))).toInt&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; /* a metric to track the maximum utilization of any thread&apos;s buffer in the last cleaning */&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; metricsGroup.newGauge(MaxBufferUtilizationPercentMetricName,&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; &#160; () =&amp;gt; maxOverCleanerThreads(_.lastStats.bufferUtilization) * 100)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;we always round down the double value, so `maxOverCleanerThreads(_.lastStats.bufferUtilization)` returns 0 always&lt;/p&gt;</description>
